                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_dard" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>dard</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>idar</orth></form><sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>далекий</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>distant</q></tr></sense><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>далеко</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>far (from)</q></tr></sense></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>dard ū mæ fændag</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>далек мой путь</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>my way is long</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>fælyǧtæn īw dard</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>я убегал далеко</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>I was running far away</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>59</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>eci doni bilæbæl, idard cardæj ew хап</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>далеко на берегу этой реки жил один хан</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>one khan lived far on the banks of this river</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>10%l4%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>nywwaǧta jæ īw dard qædy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>оставил его в отдаленном лесу</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>left him in a distant forest</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>116</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>dard ū mæ fændag</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>далек мой путь</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>my way is long</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>23</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>fælyǧtæn īw dard</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>я убегал далеко</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>I was running far away</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>59</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>eci doni bilæbæl, idard cardæj ew хап</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>далеко на берегу этой реки жил один хан</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>one khan lived far on the banks of this river</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>10%l4%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example><quote>nywwaǧta jæ īw dard qædy</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>оставил его в отдаленном лесу</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>left him in a distant forest</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_Munk."/><biblScope>116</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Начальный %ii%i- (из преверба %ivi%i-) в дигорском и конечный -%id%i не оставляют сомнения, что перед нами застывшее прош. причастие от глагола, означавшего ‘удаляться’ и т. n.: %ii-dard%i ← *%ivi-tarta%i-. Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>vi-tar-</w> <gloss><q>уносить</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>удалять</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>vitīrṇatara-</w> <gloss><q>дальше расположенный</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/> <w>vi-tar-</w> <gloss><q>переправлять</q></gloss></mentioned>. Простой глагол %itar%i- сохранился в осетинском в значении ‘гнать’, ‘угонять’ (см. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæryn"/>). Сближение со славянским <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/> <w>даль</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sla"><w>дальний</w></mentioned>,  и пр. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl>) не объясняет глагольного характера <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>dard</w></mentioned> и не поддерживается другими иранскими параллелями. Сопоставление c <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>dərəta-</w> <gloss><q>расколотый</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>30, 35</biblScope></bibl>) неприемлемо со стороны семантики.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The initial %ii%i- (from the preverb %ivi%i-) in Digor form and the final -%id%i leave no doubt that it is a lexicalized past participle form of the verb meaning ‘move away’ etc.: %ii-dard%i ← *%ivi-tarta%i-. Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><lang/> <w>vi-tar-</w> <gloss><q>take away</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w/> <gloss><q>delete</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="sa"><w>vitīrṇatara-</w> <gloss><q>further located</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="peo"><lang/> <w>vi-tar-</w> <gloss><q>transport to</q></gloss></mentioned>. A simple verb %itar%i- remains in Ossetic in the meaning ‘drive out’, ‘chase away’ (see <ref type="xr" target="#entry_tæryn"/>). Bringing together with Slavic <mentioned xml:lang="sla"><lang/> <w>dalь</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sla"><w>dalьnij</w></mentioned>,  etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Hübschmann._Oss."/><biblScope>35</biblScope></bibl>) does not explain the erbal character of <mentioned xml:lang="os"><lang/> <w>dard</w></mentioned> and is not supported by other Iranian parallels. The comparison with <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>dərəta-</w> <gloss><q>cracked</q></gloss></mentioned> (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>30, 35</biblScope></bibl>) is unacceptable due to semantic reasons.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>